dataIdInfo.idPurp:
FADs located in marine waters within the vicinity of the main Hawaiian Islands and recorded on the nautical charts. Source: NOAA Fisheries and the Hawaii Institute of Marine Biology. Data current as of June, 2016. The most up to date information can be found at https://www.hawaii.edu/HIMB/FADS/ or by calling (808) 848-2939.
Note: June 2024 - Hawaii Statewide GIS Program staff removed extraneous fields that had been added as part of 2016 GIS database conversion and were no longer needed.
For additional information, please refer to metadata at https://files.hawaii.gov/dbedt/op/gis/data/fads_nmfs.pdf or contact Hawaii Statewide GIS Program, Office of Planning and Sustainable Development, State of Hawaii; PO Box 2359, Honolulu, Hi. 96804; (808) 587-2846; email: gis@hawaii.gov; Website: https://planning.hawaii.gov/gis.
